abstract: PITTSFIELD, Mass, Sept. 29.--Alfred Ford and Firon Champine were drowned this afternoon in Pontoosuc Lake. Champine is twenty-three and Ford twenty-four years old. Both were single. The bodies were recovered after having been in the water an hour.

abstract: POUGHKEEPSIE, Sept. 29.--The steamer City of kingston, one of the bandsomest boats on the Hudson, has just been sold to the Oregon Steam Navigation Company of Portland, Oregon, and will at once be taken to that place via Cape Horn and the Straits of Magellan. The price paid was $135,000. The same company is looking for other boats along the Hudson. The Kingston will make her last trip to-morrow night.

abstract: The Evangelical Alliance for the United States will hold a national meeting in Tremont Temple, Boston, the 4th, 5th, and 6th of December next. A most attractive programme has been prepared, including the names of many eminent clergymen and laymen. The meeting is expected to equal in interest and influence the great Washington Conference of 1887. Information concerning special rates of travel and entertainment will be given to the public in due time.
